   "source": [
    "# Conditional TimeGrad Inference\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook loads a pre-trained `ConditionalTimeGrad` model and uses it to generate probabilistic forecasts on a sample from the validation set. It demonstrates the full end-to-end process:\n",
    "\n",
    "1.  **Setup**: Configure paths and parameters.\n",
    "2.  **Data Loading**: Initialize the `TimeGradDataModule` to access the validation data and the inverse transformation logic.\n",
    "3.  **Model Loading**: Instantiate the model architecture and load the saved weights from a checkpoint.\n",
    "4.  **Prediction**: Run the `model.predict()` method to generate a distribution of future scenarios.\n",
    "5.  **Inverse Transform**: Convert the model's output from the scaled, PCA-reduced space back into the original (denoised) price space.\n",
    "6.  **Visualization**: Plot the historical context, the ground truth future, the mean forecast, and the uncertainty interval."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1. Setup and Configuration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "import os\n",
    "sys.path.append('FinD_Generator')\n",
    "\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from src.data_loader import TimeGradDataModule\n",
    "from src.data_collector import DataCollector\n",
    "from src.models import create_conditional_timegrad\n",
    "from src import config\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- Configuration ---\n",
    "CHECKPOINT_PATH = 'checkpoints/best_model.pt'\n",
    "SAMPLE_IDX = 15      # Which sample from the validation set to plot\n",
    "NUM_SAMPLES = 200    # Number of Monte Carlo samples for prediction\n",
    "DEVICE = 'cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu'\n",
    "PLOT_OUTPUT_DIR = 'plots'"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2. Load Data Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "We instantiate the `TimeGradDataModule` which handles all preprocessing. This is crucial because it contains the fitted scalers and PCA objects needed to inverse-transform the model's output back to an interpretable scale."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"📊 Loading data pipeline...\")\n",
    "collector = DataCollector()\n",
    "dfs = collector.collect_all_data()\n",
    "\n",
    "dm = TimeGradDataModule(\n",
    "    data_dict=dfs,\n",
    "    seq_len=config.DEFAULT_SEQ_LEN,\n",
    "    forecast_horizon=config.DEFAULT_HORIZON,\n",
    "    batch_size=1,  # We only need one sample at a time for inference\n",
    "    device=DEVICE\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# This runs the full preprocessing and fits the scalers/PCA on the training set\n",
    "dm.preprocess_and_split()\n",
    "dm.build_datasets()\n",
    "\n",
    "val_loader = dm.val_dataloader()\n",
    "print(f\"✅ Data pipeline loaded. Validation set has {len(dm.val_set)} samples.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3. Load Pre-trained Model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(f\"🏗️ Loading model from {CHECKPOINT_PATH}...\")\n",
    "checkpoint = torch.load(CHECKPOINT_PATH, map_location=DEVICE)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get dimensions from a sample batch to instantiate the model with the correct architecture\n",
    "sample_batch = next(iter(val_loader))\n",
    "cond_dynamic_dim = sample_batch['cond_dynamic'].shape[-1]\n",
    "cond_static_dim = sample_batch['cond_static'].shape[-1]\n",
    "\n",
    "model = create_conditional_timegrad(\n",
    "    cond_dynamic_dim=cond_dynamic_dim,\n",
    "    cond_static_dim=cond_static_dim,\n",
    ").to(DEVICE)\n",
    "\n",
    "model.load_state_dict(checkpoint['model_state_dict'])\n",
    "model.eval() # Set model to evaluation mode\n",
    "print(\"✅ Model loaded successfully.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4. Select a Sample and Generate Forecast"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get the specific sample we want to plot\n",
    "if SAMPLE_IDX >= len(dm.val_set):\n",
    "    raise ValueError(f\"SAMPLE_IDX {SAMPLE_IDX} is out of bounds for validation set of size {len(dm.val_set)}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "val_iterator = iter(val_loader)\n",
    "for _ in range(SAMPLE_IDX + 1):\n",
    "    inference_batch = next(val_iterator)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"🔍 Running inference on sample index {SAMPLE_IDX}...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate the probabilistic forecast\n",
    "with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "    predictions_scaled = model.predict(\n",
    "        cond_dynamic=inference_batch['cond_dynamic'],\n",
    "        cond_static=inference_batch['cond_static'],\n",
    "        num_samples=NUM_SAMPLES\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Prediction complete.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5. Inverse Transform Data for Plotting\n",
    "\n",
    "The model predicts the first principal component of the scaled, denoised target variables. To make the plot meaningful, we must reverse this process:\n",
    "1.  **Reconstruct PCA**: Create a full PCA vector from the single predicted component.\n",
    "2.  **Inverse PCA**: Transform the PCA vector back into the multi-dimensional scaled space.\n",
    "3.  **Inverse Scaler**: Transform the scaled data back to the original price/value range.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is handled by the `dm.inverse_transform_target` method."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
